What you need to know:

Whereas Governor Lee Kinyanjui has ruled out chances of rescinding his decision to lock the matatus out of the Central Business District (CBD), the operators have vowed not to relent in their push to be allowed back there.Led by Central Rift Matatu Owners Association Chairman Steve Muli, they accused Mr Kinyanjui of discrimination, saying they are being kept off the CBD whereas hawkers are allowed to operate from there.